-- в”Ђв”Ђ Runway в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$An AI research and applied media company best known for its Gen-4 family of generative video and image models used by filmmakers, advertisers, and creative teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium subscription with monthly credit allowances, billed monthly or annually$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free plan with 125 one-time credits; paid plans from $12 per month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2018, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Roughly 480-500 employees as of 2026$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$New York City, New York, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Runway Review 2026: Gen-4 AI Video Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$What Runway's Gen-4 AI video and image platform costs, how its credit-based plans work, and who the tool suits, based on verified company facts.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Runway, legally Runway AI Inc. and commonly known by its product name Runway ML, is an AI research and applied media company founded in 2018 by Cristobal Valenzuela, Alejandro Matamala, and Anastasis Germanidis, who met while studying at New York University's Tisch School of the Arts ITP program. The company is headquartered in New York City, with additional offices reported in San Francisco, Seattle, London, and Tel Aviv, and operates largely remote-first across North America and Europe. By 2026 Runway had grown to roughly 480 to 500 employees according to workforce data providers, up sharply from its early startup days, and had raised a total of about $860 million across seven funding rounds, including a Series E round of $315 million closed in February 2026. Its valuation rose from about $3 billion in April 2025 to roughly $5.3 billion by February 2026, with revenue estimates cited around $300 million in annualized recurring revenue. Runway is best known for its Gen-4 family of generative AI models, which target character, location, and object consistency across scenes for professional film, advertising, and creative production, competing directly with offerings like Kling, Google's Veo, and Luma's Ray models. The platform also offers Gen-4.5 video generation, AI image generation using both Runway's own models and third-party models such as Nano Banana Pro, text-to-speech, and a browser-based video editor. Pricing runs on a freemium, credit-based model. The Free plan offers 125 one-time credits along with limited video editor projects and 5GB of asset storage, with generations carrying a watermark. The Standard plan costs $12 per month billed annually, or $15 per month billed monthly, and includes 625 credits per month, roughly 52 seconds of Gen-4.5 video, full access to Runway's AI image and video models, 4K upscaling, and no watermark. The Pro plan is $28 per month annually, or $35 monthly, with 2,250 credits per month, custom voice creation, and 500GB of storage. The Max plan is $76 per month annually, or $95 monthly, with 9,500 credits per month and credit rollover of up to one month. An Enterprise plan with custom credit packages, SSO, workspace analytics, and priority support is available for larger organizations. Runway targets professional and semi-professional creative users, from independent filmmakers to marketing and advertising teams, who need fast iteration on AI-generated video and image content rather than casual hobbyist use.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '82e23514-860e-4179-aa6e-cc95f88d7372';

