-- в”Ђв”Ђ Rybbit в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$An open-source, cookieless web analytics platform positioned as a simpler, privacy-friendly alternative to Google Analytics, available as a hosted service or self-hosted deployment.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium SaaS with a fully feature-complete self-hosted open-source option under AGPL-3$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (3,000 events per month); paid plans from $13 per month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2025, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Very small team, originally built and launched by a single indie developer$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Rybbit Review 2026: Pricing and Google Analytics Alternative$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$How Rybbit's cookieless, open-source web analytics platform is priced, what its self-hosted option includes, and how it compares as a Google Analytics alternative.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Rybbit is an open-source, privacy-first web analytics platform designed as a simpler, cookie-free alternative to Google Analytics. It was built by indie developer Bill Yang and publicly launched on April 15, 2025 after roughly 110 days of development, growing to more than 10,000 GitHub stars within its first year, according to the project's own reporting. Rybbit's source code is licensed under AGPL-3, and the company describes remaining open source as a permanent core value rather than a temporary growth strategy. On the privacy side, Rybbit does not use cookies at all and anonymizes visitors with randomly generated display names such as Magenta Emu or Aqua Meerkat instead of tracking individual identifiers. Its hosted cloud service is run out of infrastructure located in Germany, within the European Union, which the company positions as giving it GDPR compliance by default for hosted customers. Rybbit offers three tiers on its hosted cloud plan. The Free plan includes 3,000 events per month on a single site at no cost. The Standard plan is $19 per month billed monthly, or $13 per month billed annually, and covers 100,000 events per month across up to five sites with up to three team members. The Pro plan is $39 per month billed monthly, or $26 per month billed annually, and removes the site and team member caps entirely while adding session replay and five-year data retention. Rybbit also offers a self-hosted deployment that is free under its AGPL-3 open-source license; unlike some competitors that reserve advanced functionality for paid cloud customers, Rybbit's self-hosted build is reported to be feature-complete, including session replay, funnels, and the same dashboard available to paying cloud customers. Product features across both hosted and self-hosted deployments include real-time dashboards, funnel analysis, session replay on higher tiers, and a simplified interface that reviewers describe as easier to use than Google Analytics 4 while offering more depth than minimalist privacy analytics tools like Plausible. Because it was founded in 2025 and is still run by a very small team, Rybbit is a young, fast-growing product rather than an established enterprise analytics vendor, which appeals to developers and privacy-conscious site owners who want control over their analytics stack but may carry more execution risk than legacy analytics platforms with larger support organizations.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '2c1b5e9c-512c-48b9-b212-f464f5c0a339';

